events.name: LSU Tigers at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: No. 1 LSU gained the inside track to the BCS title game, beating No. 2 Alabama 9-6 on Drew Alleman's 25-yard field goal in overtime after a fierce defensive struggle in which neither team reached the end zone Saturday night.

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Brandon Weeden threw for a school record 502 yards and four touchdowns, and Joseph Randle scored the final, tiebreaking 23-yard touchdown with 2:16 remaining to lift No. 3 Oklahoma State to a 52-45 victory against No. 17 Kansas State on Saturday night.

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Andrew Luck shook off the rain and the chill to throw for 206 yards and three touchdowns in No. 4 Stanford's 38-13 victory over Oregon State on Saturday.

events.name: Boise State Broncos at UNLV Rebels

headlines.description: Kellen Moore threw five touchdown passes to become college football's winningest quarterback and No. 5 Boise State brushed off a first-half scare from UNLV in a 48-21 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Moore tosses 5 TDs as Boise State drops UNLV

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Landry Jones threw two touchdown passes and Roy Finch and Blake Bell added short TD runs on consecutive possessions and Oklahoma pulled away from Texas A&M 41-25 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oklahoma pounds Texas A&M but loses Broyles

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Tyler Wilson threw for 299 yards and two touchdowns as No. 8 Arkansas held on for a 44-28 win over No. 10 South Carolina on Saturday.

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Washington Huskies

headlines.description: No. 6 Oregon 34, Washington 17
headlines.shortLinkText: Turnovers doom Washington in loss to Oregon

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Second-string quarterback Kain Colter ran for two touchdowns and passed for another to lead Northwestern to a 28-25 upset of No. 9 Nebraska on Saturday.

events.name: Houston Cougars at UAB Blazers

headlines.description: Case Keenum threw for 407 yards to become the most prolific passer in NCAA history and he added his first two rushing touchdowns of the season to lead Houston past UAB 56-13 on Saturday night.

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Marcus Coker ran for 132 yards and a pair of touchdown and Iowa held off a late Michigan rally to beat the 13th-ranked Wolverines 24-16 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa wins as Michigan's final drive falls short

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Le'Veon Bell's 35-yard touchdown run with 10:58 remaining helped No. 15 Michigan State hold off upset-minded Minnesota 31-24 on Saturday.

events.name: New Mexico State Aggies at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray threw five second-quarter touchdown passes, former walk-on receiver Brandon Harton ran for 98 yards and Georgia won its seventh straight game by cruising past New Mexico State 63-16 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia scores 42 in 2nd quarter, rips NMSU

events.name: Arizona State Sun Devils at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Derrick Coleman scored the go-ahead touchdown for UCLA on a 1-yard run with 49 seconds to play, and Alex Garoutte missed a 46-yard field goal attempt as time expired in the Bruins' 29-28 victory over No. 20 Arizona State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCLA upsets Arizona State thanks to missed FG

events.name: Purdue Boilermakers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Montee Ball rushed for a career-high 223 yards with three touchdowns and No. 19 Wisconsin rebounded from back-to-back losses with a 62-17 rout of Purdue on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wisconsin back on track after Ball runs for 223

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Freshman Joe Bergeron ran for 191 yards and three touchdowns and Texas used another punishing rushing performance to rout Texas Tech 52-20 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas (439 rush yards) runs by  Texas Tech

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Teddy Bridgestone threw for one touchdown, Andrew Johnson returned a blocked field goal for another score and Louisville shocked No. 24 West Virginia 38-35 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Louisville stuns W. Virginia to win 3rd in row

events.name: Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles at East Carolina Pirates

headlines.description: Jamie Collins scored on a 97-yard interception return and Deron Wilson added one of 79 yards to lead Southern Mississippi to a 48-28 win over East Carolina on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Collins' interception return boosts Southern Miss

events.name: Syracuse Orange at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: Quarterback Scott McCummings ran for two touchdowns and Lyle McCombs ran for 152 yards and a score to lead Connecticut to a 28-21 win over Syracuse on Saturday, keeping alive the Huskies hopes for a winning season.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCummings sparks UConn past Cuse in fourth

events.name: James Madison Dukes at New Hampshire Wildcats

headlines.description: New Hampshire 28, James Madison 10

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Braxton Miller ran for two scores including a record 81-yarder and Travis Howard ended Indiana's last chance at tying it with an interception, leading Ohio State to a 34-20 victory on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miller runs for 2 TDs as Ohio St. wins 3 in a row

events.name: Ball State Cardinals at Eastern Michigan Eagles

headlines.description: Ball St. 33, E. Michigan 31

events.name: Vanderbilt Commodores at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Jeff Demps ran for a career-high 158 yards and two touchdowns, shouldering the load because of Chris Rainey's ankle injury, and Florida beat Vanderbilt 26-21 Saturday to end a four-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powered by Demps, Gators end 4-game skid

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: Zach Guyer kicked a 42-yard field goal with 4:30 left to give Iowa State the lead, and backup running back Jeff Woody helped the Cyclones run out the clock in a 13-10 victory over Kansas on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa St. turns back Kansas with late field goal

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Perry Jones ran for 139 yards and two touchdowns, Michael Rocco threw for two scores, and Virginia beat Maryland 31-13 Saturday to become bowl eligible for the first time since 2007.
headlines.shortLinkText: Virginia bowl eligible for first time since 2007

events.name: North Carolina Tar Heels at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description:
Mike Glennon threw a touchdown pass to help
North Carolina State beat North Carolina 13-0 on Saturday, earning
its fifth straight win against its nearby rival.
headlines.shortLinkText: NC State shuts out UNC for 1st time since 1960

events.name: Duke Blue Devils at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Lamar Miller ran for two touchdowns and became Miami's first 1,000-yard rusher since 2002, Jacory Harris passed for three first-half scores and the Hurricanes scored on their first five possessions to roll past Duke 49-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miller tops 1,000 yards as Canes top Blue Devils

events.name: Tulane Green Wave at SMU Mustangs

headlines.description: SMU 45, Tulane 24

events.name: Ole Miss Rebels at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Maxwell Smith threw for 283 yards and the go-ahead touchdown in the fourth quarter as Kentucky beat Mississippi 30-13 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Frosh QB Smith leads Kentucky past Mississippi

headlines.description: Coastal Carolina 15, Presbyterian 8

events.name: Washington State Cougars at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Embattled California quarterback Zach Maynard threw for 118 yards and a touchdown before leaving with an injury, Isi Sofele ran for 138 yards and a TD and California routed Washington State 30-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: QB Maynard paces Cal's rout of Washington St.

events.name: Utah Utes at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Jon Hays threw for 199 yards and a pair of touchdowns, and Utah's defense hounded Arizona quarterback Nick Foles into a pair of big mistakes en route to a 34-21 win over the Wildcats on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah hounds Arizona QB Foles to pick up victory

events.name: South Florida Bulls at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: San San Te kicked a 37-yard field goal in overtime and Rutgers snapped a two-game losing streak and become bowl eligible with a 20-17 victory over South Florida on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Te's 37-yard FG in OT pushes Rutgers by USF

events.name: Cincinnati Bearcats at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Zach Collaros threw for 214 yards and ran for two touchdowns as Cincinnati took firm control of the Big East race with a 26-23 win over Pittsburgh on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cincy takes control of Big East

events.name: Missouri Tigers at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Robert Griffin III threw for 406 yards and three touchdowns and ran for another, and Terrance Ganaway ran for touchdowns of 38 and 80 yards, leading Baylor to a 42-39 victory over Missouri on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor rides school-best 697 yards past Mizzou

events.name: Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Tauren Poole ran for two touchdowns as Tennessee beat Middle Tennessee 24-0 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole powers Vols past Middle Tennessee

events.name: Tennessee-Martin Skyhawks at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Vick Ballard rushed for 102 yards and two touchdowns to lead Mississippi State to a 55-17 victory over Tennessee-Martin Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miss. St. racks up 570 yards in rolling UT-Martin
